{"title_page": "Gideon Hausner", "text_new": "{{Infobox member of the Knesset\n| image= GidH.jpg\n| birth_date = 26 September 1915\n| birth_place = [[Lemberg]], [[Austria-Hungary]]\n| death_date = {{death date and age|1990|11|15|1915|09|26|df=y}}\n| death_place =\n| Knesset(s) = [[1965 Israeli legislative election|6]], [[1969 Israeli legislative election|7]], [[1973 Israeli legislative election|8]], [[1977 Israeli legislative election|9]]\n| party1 = [[Independent Liberals (Israel)|Independent Liberals]]\n| partyyears1 = 1965\u20131974\n| party2 = [[Independent Liberals (Israel)|Independent Liberals]]\n| partyyears2 = 1977\u20131981\n| minister1 = [[Minister without Portfolio]]\n| ministeryears1 = 1974\u20131977\n| otherroles1 = [[Attorney General of Israel|Attorney General]]\n| otherrolesyears1 = 1960\u20131963\n| otherroles2 = Chairman of the council of [[Yad Vashem]] \n| otherrolesyears2 = 1969\u20131989\n}}\n\n'''Gideon Hausner''' ({{lang-he-n|\u05d2\u05d3\u05e2\u05d5\u05df \u05d4\u05d0\u05d5\u05d6\u05e0\u05e8}}{{lrm}}, 26 September 1915 \u2013 15 November 1990) was an [[Israel]]i jurist and politician. Between 1960 and 1963, he served as [[Attorney General of Israel|Attorney General]] and was later elected to the Knesset and served in the [[Cabinet of Israel|cabinet]].\n\nHausner is most widely known for heading the team of [[prosecutor]]s at the [[war crimes]] trial of [[Adolf Eichmann]] in [[Jerusalem]] in 1961. Hausner is generally credited with exposing the [[Holocaust]] to the world in bold cross-examinations of Eichmann, but was criticized for showmanship.<ref>{{cite web|last1=Arendt|first1=Hannah|title=Eichmann in Jerusalem|url=https://www.newyorker.com/magazine/1963/02/16/eichmann-in-jerusalem-i|website=The New Yorker|accessdate=15 December 2017|date=9 February 1963}}</ref> His judicial skill also set the precedent that the defense [[Nuremberg Defense|\"I was only following orders\"]] is not valid if such orders are wholly criminal and illegal. The prosecution succeeded in proving Eichmann's guilt, and Eichmann was found guilty on all charges, including [[Crime against humanity|crimes against humanity]] and crimes against the Jewish people. He was sentenced to death.\n\n==Biography==\nHausner was born in [[Lemberg]], then the capital of [[Kingdom of Galicia and Lodomeria|Galicia]], a province of [[Austria-Hungary]] (now [[Ukraine]]), to Polish-Jewish economist rabbi and Zionist [[Bernard Hausner]], who was later member of Polish [[Sejm]] (parliament).<ref>[https://www.encyclopedia.com/religion/encyclopedias-almanacs-transcripts-and-maps/hausner-bernard Hausner, Bernard]</ref> He [[aliyah|immigrated]] to [[Mandatory Palestine]] from [[Poland]] in 1927, when his father took the post of Economic Advisor to the Polish Government first in Haifa and later in Tel-Aviv. Hausner attended high school in [[Tel Aviv]] before studying philosophy at the [[Hebrew University of Jerusalem]] and then law at the Jerusalem Law School.<ref>[https://www.knesset.gov.il/mk/eng/mk_eng.asp?mk_individual_id_t=373 Gideon Hausner: Particulars] Knesset website</ref> He spoke Polish, Hebrew, Yiddish, English and German.\n\nHe was a member of the [[Haganah]], during the [[1948 Arab-Israeli War]] he served in the [[Etzioni Brigade]]. After the conflict he worked as a military prosecutor, and then as president of the military court.\n\nIn 1960, he was appointed Attorney General, but resigned from the post in 1963 and pursued a career in politics. He was elected to the Knesset in 1965 as a member of the [[Independent Liberals (Israel)|Independent Liberals]], having previously been active in the [[Progressive Party (Israel)|Progressive Party]] (the Independent Liberals were a breakaway group of mostly Progressive Party members following the party's merger into [[Gahal]]). He was re-elected in 1969 and 1973, and resigned from the Knesset upon being appointed a [[Minister without Portfolio]] in 1974 as part of Golda Meir's cabinet. Re-elected in 1977 as the only member of the party, he lost his seat in the [[1981 Israeli legislative election|1981 elections]] when the party failed to cross the [[Election threshold|electoral threshold]].\n\nHe was also the chairman of the council of [[Yad Vashem]] (1969\u20131989).<ref>[https://hausner.school/about/history-biography Biography]</ref>\n\nHe was married with Judith, they had two childeren: Tamar and Amos,<ref>[https://www.nytimes.com/1990/11/17/obituaries/gideon-hausner-75-dies-in-israel-headed-prosecution-of-eichmann.html Gideon Hausner, 75, Dies in Israel; Headed Prosecution of Eichmann]</ref>\nHis daughter is Tami Raveh-Hausner, chairwoman of [[HaHadashot 12]], she is married to advocate [[Yehuda Raveh]].<ref>[[Yedioth Ahronoth]], December 15, 1998.</ref>\n\n==Bibliography==\n*{{cite book|title=Justice in Jerusalem|year=1966|publisher=Harper & Row|location=New York}}\n*{{cite book|title=Holocaust on Trial|year=1988|publisher=`Am `oved|location=Tel Aviv|isbn=965-13-0478-2|language=Hebrew}}\n\n==References==\n{{reflist}}\n\n==External links==\n{{commons category}}\n*{{MKlink|id=373}}\n\n{{Attorneys General of Israel}}\n{{Authority control}}\n\n{{DEFAULTSORT:Hausner, Gideon}}\n[[Category:1915 births]]\n[[Category:1990 deaths]]\n[[Category:Government ministers of Israel]]\n[[Category:Prosecutors]]\n[[Category:Attorneys General of Israel]]\n[[Category:Haganah members]]\n[[Category:Independent Liberals (Israel) leaders]]\n[[Category:Jews from Galicia (Eastern Europe)]]\n[[Category:People from the Kingdom of Galicia and Lodomeria]]\n[[Category:Ukrainian Jews]]\n[[Category:Polish Jews]]\n[[Category:Polish emigrants to Mandatory Palestine]]\n[[Category:People from Lviv]]\n[[Category:Adolf Eichmann]]\n[[Category:20th-century Israeli lawyers]]\n[[Category:Members of the 6th Knesset (1965\u20131969)]]\n[[Category:Members of the 7th Knesset (1969\u20131974)]]\n[[Category:Members of the 8th Knesset (1974\u20131977)]]\n[[Category:Members of the 9th Knesset (1977\u20131981)]]\n",